{
  "stem": "10905.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "3 And 1/2 years.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, we  may come for weekends to Subotica, you know, but our primary-- primary residence was in Belgrade, yes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have a sister-- an old sister.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was born February 14, 1935.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she was 2 and 1/2 years older than me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Myriam.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "M-Y-R-I-A-M.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her current last name is Danber, D-A-N-B-E-R.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she's a retired school teacher.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I do.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, let's-- I'd like to go over-- well, before the war, my whole-- my-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] my family life primarily was in Belgrade, except for the high holidays, when we would come to Subotica to be with the entire family.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father's family was not a wealthy family, but his father was a shamas in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was a very, very hard working man.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was able to send, on his meager income, two sons to the university, which was a very, very big thing at the time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He sent my Uncle Joseph, after whom I am named, to Berlin, where he was a-- a chemical engineer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was in a laboratory that were working on the development of plastics.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were working with Bakelite.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And unfortunately, the blast furnace oven blew up and crushed him and killed him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My dad was studying medicine in Berlin at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he got married, and when he had his first male child, his only male child, I was named after my Uncle Joseph.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's how come my name is Joseph.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My mother's family came from what was very well to do, who became very well to do.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
